<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="206" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="15" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,151,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="206">Etymology</emphasis>
. From the latin 
<emphasis box="[519,605,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="206">chasma</emphasis>
(= gorge, steep-sided depression), in reference to Oologskloof Canyon, where both known localities are situated.
</paragraph>
